        <updateDate>2022-04-22T19:10:03Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Hotels for Heroes Act of 2022</strong></p> <p>This bill requires public lodging establishments to waive any minimum age requirements to obtain accommodation for members of the Armed Forces who present a valid identification card and seek to obtain accommodation while under military orders or on authorized military leave. A knowing violation of this requirement is punishable by fine.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
